# \U0001f9e0 <type>(scope): short summary
#
# Type (choose one):
#   feat       \u2013 \U0001f527 new tool, module, or feature
#   fix        \u2013 \U0001f41b bug or issue fixed
#   docs       \u2013 \U0001f4d8 README, inline docs, or comments
#   style      \u2013 \U0001f3a8 formatting, spacing, casing (no logic changes)
#   refactor   \u2013 \u267b\ufe0f code cleanup or restructuring (no feature change)
#   test       \u2013 \u2705 unit, integration, fuzzing, or regression tests
#   chore      \u2013 \U0001f501 maintenance, deps, configs, meta
#   perf       \u2013 \u26a1 speed, efficiency, reduced resource use
#   ci         \u2013 \U0001f916 CI/CD configs, pipelines
#   build      \u2013 \U0001f3d7\ufe0f build scripts, Dockerfiles, compile stuff
#   sec        \u2013 \U0001f510 security fix, hardening, validation, CVE response
#
# Scope (optional): area or context (e.g., cli, api, jwt, netsec, parser, etc.)
#
# Example:
#   feat(cli): add payload encoding module
#   fix(netsec): prevent SSRF through DNS rebinding
#   sec(parser): patch unsanitized input injection
#   chore: update shellcheck ruleset
#
# --------------------
# Body (optional, supports markdown)
#
# Explain *why* the change exists, edge cases handled, and any context.
#
# - What changed technically?
# - Any tests added or commands to verify?
# - Impacts on deployment, integrations, security posture?
#
# --------------------
# Footer (optional)
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: describe breaking behavior (if any)
# Closes: #ticket | Related: #issue | Co-authored-by:

